# __MODULE__

An IterForge experiment loop scaffolded by `iterforge init`.

> Program the research loop, not every experiment.

## What is mutable vs frozen

- Mutable surface: `candidates/` and `logs/agent_journal.md`.
- Frozen surface: `evals/`, `cmd/`, `policy.yaml`, `go.mod`.

Improve the candidate. Do not edit the evaluator, the golden set, or the
results log.

## The loop

Run one scored experiment:

    make run NOTE="trim and lowercase"

Each run scores `candidates.Transform` against `evals/golden_set.jsonl` and
appends one JSON line to `logs/results.jsonl`.

Summarize progress:

    make summarize

Before considering a change complete:

    make check

## Score

The primary metric is accuracy (fraction of golden cases matched exactly), with
a hard gate `min_accuracy` defined in `policy.yaml`. A run that drops below the
gate exits non-zero and is recorded as failed.

## Adapt it

Replace the task: change `candidates.Transform`, the `evals` evaluator, and
`golden_set.jsonl` to your problem. Keep the mutable/frozen split intact.
